Since `rdflib.namespace.Namespace` inherits from `unicode`, certain vocabulary names clashes with methods on unicode objects, and have to be accessed using `__getitem__` (e.g. `NS['upper']`) instead of `NS.upper`.

A possible improvement (for 5.0, since it would be backwards incompatible) would be to either just not inherit from `unicode`, or to add something like:

    def __getattribute__(self, name):
        return Namespace.term(self, name)

to `Namespace`. Any need to use `unicode` methods on a `Namespace` instance would then have to be done using `unicode(DCTERMS).title()` (or `unicode.title(DCTERMS)` if its inheritance is kept).

